{"title":"State Bikes Launches the  4130 Trail, a Hardtail Shredder for Everyone","link":"https://bikerumor.com/state-bikes-4130-trail-hardtail/","date":1745326800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photos / State Bicycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Arizona’s State Bicycles has become known for offering great bikes <span>at very reasonable prices, like their updated <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/first-look-state-bicycles-affordable-updated-4130-all-road-gravel-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">4130 Allroad</a></span>. Well, the new <a href=\"https://www.statebicycle.com/collections/4130-trail-hardtail-mountain-bike\" target=\"_blank\">State 4130 Trail</a> is no exception. The 4130 Trail is a perfectly capable hardtail that looks like it’s got great all-around geometry to shralp your local single track, or take on a bikepacking trip.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-first-pic-e1745257020924.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"634\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-first-pic-e1745257020924.webp\" alt=\"State Bikes 4130 Trail first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-first-pic-e1745257020924.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-first-pic-e1745257020924-297x147.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-first-pic-e1745257020924-120x59.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-first-pic-e1745257020924-768x380.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / State Bicycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s go over some of the 4130 Trail features…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial.webp\" alt=\"State Bikes 4130 Trail mustard partial\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-mustard-partial-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Progressive Trail Geo</strong><br />The 4130 Trail rocks a slack 65° head angle, and a low top tube paired with a long front-center. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel.webp\" alt=\"State Bikes 4130 Trail rear wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-rear-wheel-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A Universal Deraileur Hanger (UDH) makes the 4130 Trail virtually future-proof and ready for a modern drivetrain if that suits the user. Plus, it allows for easier component selection with broader options (and easier sourcing of replacement hangers).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side.webp\" alt=\"State Bikes 4130 Trail purp front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-purp-front-side-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Internal Dropper Routing<br /></strong>The 4130 Trail combines dropper post internal routing and a 31.6 seatpost diameter, making upgrading to a dropper a breeze. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Threaded Bottom Bracket (73mm BSA)</strong><br />Reliable, creak-free, and easy-peasy to service. ‘Nuff said.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>More Mounting Points</strong><br />The 4130 Trail comes with triple bottle cage mounts on the down tube, because the bike is geared to being versatile and ready for any adventure. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork.webp\" alt=\"State Bikes 4130 Trail fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-fork-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Rock Shox Psylo Silver RC – 130mm travel, 35mm stanchions</strong><br />At the 4130 Trail’s retail price, you’d expect to see a budget offering in the suspension fork category, but not in this case. The Rock Shox Psylo Silver RC rocks beefy 35mm stanchions, Motion Control damper and Solo Air spring. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>SRAM DB4 Brake Upgrade</strong><br />For only $150, you can upgrade the 4130 Trail’s brakes with the new SRM DB4. These are low-maintenance, mineral oil system that provides some serious stopping power. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>4130 Trail Retail, Sizes, &amp; Upgrade Options</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set.webp\" alt=\"State Bikes 4130 Trail frame set\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bikes-4130-Trail-frame-set-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $1,499 </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colors: West Sunset, and Patina Gold</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes:<br />XS/S: 5’1″ to 5’5″<br />S/M: 5’5″ to 5’10”<br />M/L: 5’10” to 6’1″<br />X-Large: 6’1″ to 6’5″</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop.webp\" alt=\"State Bicycles 4130 Trail drop\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-drop-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>WHEELSET:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>WTB i30 TCS 29” Tubeless-Ready Rims – Wide profile for optimal tire support and better traction.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Boost Hubs (110/148mm, Sealed Bearings) – Reliable, smooth, and built to last.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tubeless Valves Included</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WTB Trailboss TCS 29 x 2.4” Tubeless-Ready – Aggressive tread for grip and speed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Upgrade:</strong> Enve AM30 Carbon Wheels ($999.99) – $1400 Retail Value</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2.webp\" alt=\"State Bicycles 4130 Trail corner 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-2-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner.webp\" alt=\"State Bicycles 4130 Trail corner\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-corner-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>DRIVETRAIN:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>1×11 Speed MicroShift XLE – Simple, efficient, and built for real-world durability.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Crankset: SBC 32T Narrow-Wide (165mm)– Direct-mount for better chain retention.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cassette: 11-46T – Enough range to climb like a goat and rip the descents.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>KMC X11 Chain – Reliable shifting with corrosion-resistant plating</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Upgrade:</strong> SRAM Eagle AXS – 12-speed Wireless (11-50) – ($499.99)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose.webp\" alt=\"State Bicycles 4130 Trail pose\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-pose-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>BRAKES:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Tektro Hydraulic Disc Brakes (HD-M275) w/ 180mm Rotors – Confidence-inspiring stopping power in all conditions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>COCKPIT:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Handlebars: SBC Low Rise, 770mm Wide, 35mm Clamp – Wide and stable for all-mountain control.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stem: SBC 3D-Forged Alloy (35mm Clamp) – Short and responsive for precise handling.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>SEATPOST &amp; SADDLE: </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Saddle: Trail-Ready PU Pad with Steel Rails – Ride comfortably all day.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Standard Seapost – SBC 31.6mm – Future-proofed for an easy dropper upgrade with quick-release seatpost clamp or on-the-trail adjustments</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Upgrade: </strong>PNW Components’ Range Dropper &amp; Dropper Lever – $199.99</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>MAX TIRE CLEARANCE:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame: 29” Wheels: Up to 2.6” / 27.5” Wheels: Up To 3.0”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fork: 29″ Wheels: Up to 2.6″ / 27.5′ Wheels: N/A</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: TBD</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>4130 Trail Geo</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic.webp\" alt=\"State Bicycles 4130 Trail last pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/State-Bicycles-4130-Trail-last-pic-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Geometry</strong></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td></td><td><strong>XS / S</strong></td><td><strong>S / M</strong></td><td><strong>M / L</strong></td><td><strong>XL</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Seat Tube Length(mm)</strong></td><td>380</td><td>405</td><td>430</td><td>460</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Top Tube Length(mm)</strong></td><td>594.7</td><td>622.6</td><td>645.5</td><td>673.3</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Head Tube Angle(Degree)</strong></td><td>65</td><td>65</td><td>65</td><td>65</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Seat Tube Angle(Degree)</strong></td><td>74.5</td><td>74.4</td><td>74.4</td><td>74.4</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Head Tube Length(mm)</strong></td><td>100</td><td>110</td><td>120</td><td>130</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Front Center(mm)</strong></td><td>737.6</td><td>766.7</td><td>790.9</td><td>820</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Rear Center(mm)</strong></td><td>426.5</td><td>426.5</td><td>426.5</td><td>426.5</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Wheelbase(mm)</strong></td><td>1158.2</td><td>1187.5</td><td>1211.7</td><td>1240.9</td></tr><tr><td><strong>BB Height（27.5*3.0 Tire）(mm)</strong></td><td>312</td><td>312</td><td>312</td><td>312</td></tr><tr><td><strong>BB Height（29*2.6 Tire）(mm)</strong></td><td>321</td><td>321</td><td>321</td><td>321</td></tr><tr><td><strong>BB Drop(mm)</strong></td><td>56</td><td>56</td><td>56</td><td>56</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Reach(mm)</strong></td><td>420</td><td>445</td><td>465</td><td>490</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Stack(mm)</strong></td><td>628.3</td><td>637.4</td><td>646.5</td><td>655.5</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Standover Height（27.5*3.0 Tire）(mm)</strong></td><td>784</td><td>800</td><td>817</td><td>835</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Standover Height（29*2.6 Tire）(mm)</strong></td><td>793</td><td>809</td><td>826</td><td>844</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.statebicycle.com/\" target=\"_blank\">StateBicycle.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/state-bikes-4130-trail-hardtail/\">State Bikes Launches the  4130 Trail, a Hardtail Shredder for Everyone</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"c6ad12e315d8a95eb11cca028282d706a6258e1a2afe0c278388b9ea97960080","category":"Cycling"}